        "text": "\n1.  **Existence and Uniqueness:** A unique solution $\\Phi_t(x_0)$ exists for any"
      }, {
        "text": " starting point.\n2.  **Global Flow:** The solution exists as long as the particle doesn\u0027t hit a singularity"
      }, {
        "text": " or infinity.\n3.  **Error Bounds:** You can calculate the error of your numerical propagator precisely.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of"
      }, {
        "text": " the \"Workflow\"\nIf you are given $f(x) \u003d x^3 - x$:\n\n1.  **Partial"
